task.summary: Default task
Convert python snake_case to Java camelCase.
Remove printing the exponent and scalar from unit tests.
Added Parameterized evaluate coefs tests. They exposed a bug where the terms are not in the same order at the original polyfun in 7 out of 1000 cases.

Put comparing polynomial strings into PolyPairFactory so changes shared with all parameterized tests. Created a compare method to ignore the order of terms, just make sure they are all there. In all parameterized tests, made sure to make 20% of test cases with the astract coef constructor. Started work on refactoring simplify and related methods.
Clean up imports.
Created a test runner for the parameterized tests. Added - (minus sign) as a split delimiter in the compare unordered test.
Testing more constructors and putting repeated code into PolyPairFactory.
Test runner for non-parameterized tests.
More tests for Polynomial.of(). Wrote raiseTo() but it gives different output that to() so don't use it.
Put testlib folder in a package in the test folder. Marked test folder as test, not source.
Fix raiseTo(). Re-arranged test code again.
Fix in Coef.simply to handle 0-len term arrays. Fix in Coef.times to ignore empty terms (terms that exist with a coef of 0 and empty Atom array).
Fix bug where Atoms array was set to null instead of Atom[0]. It had downstream effects on of(), times() and plus().
Fix where trailing + appearing in poly.toString() and where there would be a +- instead of just a -.
Updated Coef.smartInsert and wrote a unit test.
Unit tests for Coef reduce, pop, push and Term reduce, pop, push.
Fully port to Term.reduce() instead of simplify in the Coef object.
Redid sorting of terms within a coef to be: constant terms go last, sort abstract terms alphanumerically, ignoring constant coef.
Fixed error where Atoms that had power 0 were messing up the sort order.
Got rid of random tests in PolynomialTest
Got rid of isLessThan tests in TermTests because the rules of sorting have changed.
Changed or deleted place, insert and times tests now that the coef auto-reduces.
updated class diagram
Ignore the string compare tests in paramaterized suite because the order of terms will be different.
